1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,437
This demo shows more than a diagnosis.

2
00:00:02,437 --> 00:00:04,360
It shows the decision process.

3
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:06,604
We start with a real incident case.

4
00:00:06,604 --> 00:00:09,041
H zero zero nine, liveness probe loop.

5
00:00:09,041 --> 00:00:10,901
The service keeps restarting.

6
00:00:10,901 --> 00:00:13,337
The liveness probe timing has drifted.

7
00:00:13,337 --> 00:00:16,864
First, we run the case with a strict threshold profile.

8
00:00:16,864 --> 00:00:19,236
The system explores a plausible path.

9
00:00:19,236 --> 00:00:20,519
It scores that path.

10
00:00:20,519 --> 00:00:22,699
It follows the available evidence.

11
00:00:22,699 --> 00:00:25,456
But the confidence does not improve enough.

12
00:00:25,456 --> 00:00:27,636
So this branch becomes a dead end.

13
00:00:27,636 --> 00:00:28,790
That is important.

14
00:00:28,790 --> 00:00:30,265
The failure is visible.

15
00:00:30,265 --> 00:00:32,445
We can see where the path stalled.

16
00:00:32,445 --> 00:00:34,433
We can see why it was rejected.

17
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:35,779
And we can backtrack.

18
00:00:35,779 --> 00:00:38,152
Now we run the exact same case again.

19
00:00:38,152 --> 00:00:39,050
Same problem.

20
00:00:39,050 --> 00:00:39,947
Same signals.

21
00:00:39,947 --> 00:00:42,127
But a different threshold profile.

22
00:00:42,127 --> 00:00:45,013
This time, the system converges more cleanly.

23
00:00:45,013 --> 00:00:47,898
So the goal is not only to produce an answer.

24
00:00:47,898 --> 00:00:50,655
The goal is to make the reasoning explicit.

25
00:00:50,655 --> 00:00:51,553
Reviewable.

26
00:00:51,553 --> 00:00:52,451
And tunable.

27
00:00:52,451 --> 00:00:56,234
Next, we switch to H zero zero six, network policy blocked.

28
00:00:56,234 --> 00:00:59,440
Here, the system reaches a valid remediation path.

29
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:01,620
But it does not act automatically.

30
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:03,929
It stops at the human decision gate.

31
00:01:03,929 --> 00:01:06,493
The operator reviews the recommendation.

32
00:01:06,493 --> 00:01:08,866
Then chooses to approve or reject it.

33
00:01:08,866 --> 00:01:10,276
That is the key point.

34
00:01:10,276 --> 00:01:11,751
The system can explore.

35
00:01:11,751 --> 00:01:12,649
Compare.

36
00:01:12,649 --> 00:01:14,060
And justify decisions.

37
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:17,971
But the final operational choice remains under human control.
